ok explores the extraordinary changes these women fought to achieve as each made her way from marginalised ‘poetess’ of the 1970s to laureate at the heart of cultural establishment in the 21st century. It looks at how they revitalised these public offices, and explores their interventions in contemporary geopolitics and national self-understanding. It considers how they shaped their roles by engaging with poetic icons of the past, by linking poetry and education, and by joining poetry with politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aNationalism and literaturezGreat Britain. 0aNationalism and literaturezIreland. 0aPoets laureatezGreat Britain. 0aPoets laureatezIreland. 0aWomen and literaturezGreat BritainxHistory. 0aWomen and literaturezIrelandxHistory. 0aWomen poets, English. 0aWomen poets, Irish. 0aWomen poets, Scottish. 0aWomen poets, Welsh. 4aLiterary Studies. 70(DE-588)4014777-00(DE-627)1063387490(DE-576)208909400aEnglisch2gnd 70(DE-588)4113622-60(DE-627)1058280680(DE-576)209478004aFrauenliteratur2gnd 70(DE-588)4171224-90(DE-627)1053964510(DE-576)209935642aNationalliteratur2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Feminist.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147448986740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474489867423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474489867/original  a978-3-11-075400-1 